The paper "Distributionally Robust Receive Combining" by Shixiong Wang, Wei Dai, and Geoffrey Ye Li investigates signal estimation in wireless transmission from a statistical machine learning perspective. The authors propose a distributionally robust receive combining framework that is insensitive to various uncertainties such as transmit signal covariance, channel matrix, channel noise covariance, channel impulse noises, power amplifier non-ideality, and limited pilot sample size. The proposed framework includes several existing combiners as special cases and derives uncertainty-aware solutions for optimal linear and nonlinear estimation. Additionally, the authors prove that ridge and kernel ridge regression methods in machine learning are distributionally robust against diagonal perturbation in feature covariance.

